Core Capacitor Commands
powershell# Sync web build to native (run after every code change)
npx cap sync android

# Copy only (no plugin updates)
npx cap copy android

# Update plugins only (no copy)
npx cap update android

# Open in Android Studio
npx cap open android

# Run directly on device/emulator
npx cap run android

# List connected devices
npx cap run android --list

Gradle / Build Commands
powershell# Clean build cache (run when builds act weird)
cd android
.\gradlew clean

# Back to project root
cd ..

# Full clean + sync + run (your go-to fix command)
cd android && .\gradlew clean && cd .. && npx cap sync android && npx cap run android

Build APK Commands
powershellcd android

# Debug APK (for testing, no signing needed)
.\gradlew assembleDebug

# Release APK (for distribution, needs signing)
.\gradlew assembleRelease

# Debug AAB (Google Play format - debug)
.\gradlew bundleDebug

# Release AAB (Google Play format - for Play Store upload)
.\gradlew bundleRelease
Output locations:
Debug APK:    android/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk
Release APK:  android/app/build/outputs/apk/release/app-release.apk
Debug AAB:    android/app/build/outputs/bundle/debug/app-debug.aab
Release AAB:  android/app/build/outputs/bundle/release/app-release.aab

Signing Release APK (required for Play Store)
powershell# Step 1 — Generate keystore (do this once only, save the file safely)
keytool -genkey -v -keystore socialsquare.jks -alias socialsquare -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 10000

# Step 2 — Add to android/app/build.gradle
gradleandroid {
    signingConfigs {
        release {
            storeFile file('socialsquare.jks')
            storePassword 'your_store_password'
            keyAlias 'socialsquare'
            keyPassword 'your_key_password'
        }
    }
    buildTypes {
        release {
            signingConfig signingConfigs.release
            minifyEnabled false
        }
    }
}
powershell# Step 3 — Build signed release
cd android
.\gradlew assembleRelease

ADB Commands (device debugging)
powershell# Check connected devices
adb devices

# Install APK manually
adb install android/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk

# View live logs (all)
adb logcat

# View logs filtered (your app only)
adb logcat | Select-String -Pattern "com.socialsquare.app|FATAL|AndroidRuntime|Capacitor"

# Clear app data on device
adb shell pm clear com.socialsquare.app

# Uninstall app from device
adb uninstall com.socialsquare.app

# Reboot device
adb reboot

React Build + Full Deploy Flow
powershell# Full flow from code change to device (run this every time)
npm run build && npx cap sync android && npx cap run android

# Full clean deploy (when something is broken)
npm run build && cd android && .\gradlew clean && cd .. && npx cap sync android && npx cap run android



